{
  "texts": [
    "Resilience to BEEAR.",
    "We evaluate the robustness of SHIP against BEEAR (Zeng et al., 2024) using Mistral models, as it is the only architecture supported by BEEAR's official implementation.",
    "BEEAR is a mitigation approach that leverages the drifts in the model's embedding space.",
    "However, our experiments in Table 9 demonstrate that BEEAR is ineffective at mitigating the backdoors introduced by SHIP, as it fails to replicate the nuanced drift patterns caused by stealthy permutation triggers.",
    "Notably, its mitigation efficacy decreases further when the triggers consist of four components, highlighting limited generalizability to complex triggers."
  ]
}